			<section>
									<div class="summary">
						<p>Validates and gets a fully-namespaced class path from an absolute or
relative physical path to a directory or file. The final class path may
be partial in that in doesn't contain the class name.</p>
					</div>
				
									<div class="description">
						<p>This method can be thought of the reverse of <code>Libraries::path()</code>.</p>
<pre><code class="language-php">lithium/tests/cases/core/ObjectTest.php -&gt; lithium\tests\cases\core\ObjectTest
lithium/tests/cases/core                -&gt; lithium\tests\cases\core
lithium/core/Object.php                 -&gt; lithium\core\Object
lithium/core/                           -&gt; lithium\core
lithium/core                            -&gt; lithium\core
</code></pre>
					</div>
							</section>

